    "## Step 1 — Understanding Data Types\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is a `dtype`?\n",
    "\n",
    "Every column in a DataFrame has a **data type** — it tells pandas how to store and process that column internally.\n",
    "\n",
    "| dtype | Meaning |\n",
    "|-------|---------|\n",
    "| `float64` | Decimal numbers |\n",
    "| `int64` | Whole numbers |\n",
    "| `object` | Text / strings |\n",
    "| `bool` | True / False |\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ **Important:** String columns do not get a `string` type in pandas.\n",
    "They are stored as `object` — keep this in mind when inspecting your data."
=======
    "## Step 1 — Groupwise Analysis with `groupby()`\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is `groupby()`?\n",
    "\n",
    "Think of `groupby()` like sorting your data into buckets.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "```\n",
    "All wines with 80 points → Bucket 1\n",
    "All wines with 81 points → Bucket 2\n",
    "All wines with 90 points → Bucket 3\n",
    "```\n",
    "Then you run a function on **each bucket separately**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is much more powerful than running a function on the whole dataset."
