    "## Step 3 — Finding Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is `NaN`?\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing values in pandas are stored as `NaN` — short for **Not a Number**.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Real value  →  87, 15.0, \"Italy\"\n",
    "Missing     →  NaN\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ NaN values are always `float64` dtype — even if the column contains integers.\n",
    "This is why a column of whole numbers sometimes shows as `float64` — it has at least one missing value.\n",
    "\n",
    "### `pd.isnull()` vs `pd.notnull()`\n",
    "\n",
    "| Function | Returns |\n",
    "|----------|--------|\n",
    "| `pd.isnull()` | `True` where value is NaN |\n",
    "| `pd.notnull()` | `True` where value is NOT NaN |"
   ]
  },
